description:
Luther Before the Diet: Martin Luther would defend his beliefs on several occasions with the most famous being at the Diet of Worms where he laid out the key foundation of his faith - the Bible and his conscience. This idea would continue to shake the church to its core once it was adopted by other believers as the shackles of superstition fell off.
